doctype html
html
  head
    title Slip slip presentation
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    link(rel='stylesheet', type='text/css', href='/home/panglesd/slip-js/example/slipIntroduction.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet', type='text/css', href='/home/panglesd/slip-js/slip.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet', type='text/css', href='/home/panglesd/slip-js/theorem.css')
    script#MathJax-script(type='text/javascript', src='https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js')
    // For the use of highlight.js
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/highlightjs/cdn-release@9.16.2/build/styles/default.min.css')
    script(src='https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/highlightjs/cdn-release@9.16.2/build/highlight.min.js')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/9.15.10/styles/default.min.css')
    // Highlight.js does not support inline coloring, this is a work-around
    style.
      .inline-code {
      display: inline;
      padding: 1px;
      }
  body
    #rootSlip.root(delay='1')
      // First slip, an introduction
      #intro.slip
        .titre Slip.js
        // Beamer style title
        .slip-body-container
          // Beamer style margin
          ul
            li #[span(emphasize-at='0')Slip.js] is a "slide" engine written in javascript.
            li(chg-visib-at='1') Its goal is to keep the best from both worlds of:
              ul
                li(chg-visib-at='1')
                  | #[span(emphasize-at='1')Beamer], its simplicity to create slides without worrying too much on presentation.
                li(chg-visib-at='2') #[span(emphasize-at='2')Prezi], which moves/zoom on a canvas, making it nice/original/showing the structure...
            li(chg-visib-at='3') This hybrid is the concept of #[span(emphasize-at='3')slip].
          .definition(title='Slip', chg-visib-at='4')
            // Beamer style definition
            | A slip is a slide without inferior boundary (the view moving step by step to show it entirely).
          .theorem(title='Fundamental Theorem of slip', chg-visib-at='5')
            // Beamer style theorem
            | Slip.js, it's slip party.
      // Second slip, the basics
      #base.slip
        .titre The basics
        .slip-body-container
          | You need to write html. This is what a minimal slip presentation looks like:
          // Sorry for the mess: including html into html is not very readable...
          //- Not sorry for the mess: in pug it is good!
          pre <code class="html">
              = '<!doctype html>\n'
              = '<html>\n'
              = '    <head>\n'
              = '	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="slip.css">\n'
              = '	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="theorem.css">\n'
              = '    </head>\n'
              = '    <body>\n'
              = '	<div class="root">\n'
              = '	    <div class="slip" id="id-slip-1"> ... </div>\n'
              = '	    <div class="slip" id="id-slip-2"> ... </div>\n'
              = '	</div>\n'
              = '       <script src="slip.js"></script>\n'
              = '    </body>\n'
              = '</html>'
              | </code>
          div(chg-visib-at="1") Or if you use #[a(href="pug") pug]:
            pre <code class="html">
                = 'doctype html\n'
                = 'head\n'
                = '  link(rel="stylesheet", type="text/css", href="slip.css")\n'
                = '  link(rel="stylesheet", type="text/css", href="theorem.css")\n'
                = 'body\n'
                = '  #rootSlip.root\n'
                = '    .slip#id-slip-1 ...\n'
                = '    .slip#id-slip-2 ...\n'
                = '  script(src="slip.js")\n'
                | </code>
              
      // Third slip, the beamer part
      #beamer-part.slip
        .titre The slide part of Slip
        .slip-body-container
          | We list the "slides" behaviour that slip can also do:
          ul
            // Highlight makes it unreadable, should be changed.
            li(chg-visib-at='1') We can make things appear step by step. This is made with the attributes #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code chg-visib-at]].  
            li(chg-visib-at='2')
              | This bullet code has #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code chg-visib-at="2"]]
            li(chg-visib-at='3 -4')
              | We hide an element by putting a negative number. This bullet code has #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code chg-visib-at="3 -4"]]. Be careful, it will soon disappear.
            li(chg-visib-at='4')
              | We can also emphasize at a specified step, using the attribute #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code emphasize-at="..."]] :
              | #[span(emphasize-at='5') emphasize-at='5'], #[span(emphasize-at='6') emphasize-at='6'], #[span(emphasize-at='6 7') emphasize-at='6 7']...
          .theorem(title="Slip's recursion theorem", chg-visib-at='8')
            | We also have environment for theorems/definitions/examples:
            pre <code class="html">
                = '<div class="theorem" title="Slip\'s recursion theorem" chg-visib-at="8">'
                | </code>
            | The #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code title]] attribute allows to choose the title.
          div(chg-visib-at='9')
            | We can also write math with \(mathjax\). This amounts to most of the things done with classic slides.

      // Fouth slip, the slip part
      #future.slip
        .titre The future: slips
        .slip-body-container
          h1 Problem
          | The problems with slides are the following:
          ul
            li(chg-visib-at='1') The elements appearing at the beginning of a slide stay much longer on screen than those appearing at the end.
            li(chg-visib-at='2') From time to time, we would like to show something that is just slightly bigger than a slide, but does not fit, and separating it in two slides is not really possible.
            li(chg-visib-at='3') The pdf format is very restricted on "interactivity".
          .block(chg-visib-at='3', title='A bit of latin')
            | Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Nulla vestibulum neque eu lectus euismod, eget congue massa ultrices. Integer et bibendum sem. Donec neque erat, laoreet et felis vitae, malesuada varius purus. Aenean lacinia tortor id justo consectetur, non volutpat est rhoncus. Praesent eget risus elit. Nullam tempus mi id erat aliquet, sit amet consequat erat volutpat. Phasellus elementum gravida nisl ut auctor. Donec quis massa a mauris tristique interdum gravida ac sem. Aliquam ligula massa, hendrerit et diam sit amet, vulputate consectetur ligula. Phasellus dictum nisl est, quis commodo nunc pellentesque vel. Nulla facilisi. Donec pharetra tellus ut auctor dignissim. Proin convallis ante in pellentesque consectetur. Pellentesque habitant morbi tristique senectus et netus et malesuada fames ac turpis egestas. Morbi tempor sem a lectus ullamcorper fringilla. Maecenas tempor metus mauris, non tincidunt ligula placerat non. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Nulla vestibulum neque eu lectus euismod, eget congue massa ultrices. Integer et bibendum sem. Donec neque erat, laoreet et felis vitae, malesuada varius purus. Aenean lacinia tortor id justo consectetur, non volutpat est rhoncus. Praesent eget risus elit. Nullam tempus mi id erat aliquet, sit amet consequat erat volutpat. Phasellus elementum gravida nisl ut auctor. Donec quis massa a mauris tristique interdum gravida ac sem.
          h1(chg-visib-at='4"') Solution!
          .theorem(chg-visib-at='4', down-at='4')
            | Slips address this!
          ul
            li(up-at='7', down-at='5', chg-visib-at='5')
              | We can move the screen to see an element below with #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code down-at]].
            li(center-at='6', chg-visib-at='6')
              | Same, we can center on an element with #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code center-at]].
            li(chg-visib-at='7')
              | If we really don't want to see what was before, we can align an element with the top of the screen with #[pre.inline-code #[code.inline-code up-at]]. Here, it is done with the first bullet.
            h3(chg-visib-at='8')
              | This is the concept of slip.js: a downward infinite slide. But slip.js is much more!
            li(chg-visib-at='9')
              | All slips are placed on a big universe &quot;universe&quot;. 
              span(chg-visib-at='11', emphasize-at='11')
                | But they are just html elements and can be placed statically, relatively or absolutely.
              pre(chg-visib-at='11').
                
            div(style='display: flex; justify-content: space-around; margin:40px;')
              #red.slip(style='background-color:red', scale='0.25', delay='1')
                .titre Choose a color
                .slip-body-container
                  div(style='color:blue; font-size:5em;text-align:center') Blue Slip
                  div(chg-visib-at='1', style='color:blue; font-size:2em;text-align:center') The presentation is structured as a tree rather than a linear presentation
                  div(chg-visib-at='2', style='color:blue; font-size:2em;text-align:center') Press "t" to hide/see the table of content
                  div(chg-visib-at='3', style='color:blue; font-size:2em;text-align:center') Click on a step or a slip to jump to it
                  div(chg-visib-at='4', style='color:blue; font-size:2em;text-align:center') The counter bottom-left reflects the tree version of a presentation
                  div(chg-visib-at='5', style='color:blue; font-size:5em;text-align:center') Blue Slip
                  div(chg-visib-at='5', style='color:blue; font-size:5em;text-align:center') Blue Slip
                  div(chg-visib-at='5', style='color:blue; font-size:5em;text-align:center') Blue Slip
                  div(chg-visib-at='5', down-at='5', style='color:blue; font-size:2em;text-align:center') Remember: slips are not of fixed height!
              #blue.slip(style='background-color:blue', scale='0.25', delay='1')
                .titre Choose a color
                .slip-body-container
                  div(style='color:red; font-size:5em;text-align:center') Red Slip
                  div(chg-visib-at='1', style='color:red; font-size:2em;text-align:center') You can navigate slip by slip with shift+left/right
                  div(chg-visib-at='2', style='color:red; font-size:2em;text-align:center') You can restart a slip with "r";
                  div(chg-visib-at='3', style='color:red; font-size:2em;text-align:center') Soon there will be more navigation fun!
            li(chg-visib-at='15')
              | We can use all JS/CSS/HTML power to make more or less useful stuff. The goal is of course to make the presentation clearer!
              ul
                li(down-at='15')
                  | Any javascript poorly written:
                  div(style='position: relative;padding: 5px;')
                    input#mouseGhost(style='transition: left 1s; left:0px; font-size: 1.5em; visibility:hidden', type='button', value='Click me!')
                    input#mouse(style='transition: left 1s; position:absolute; left:0px; font-size: 1.5em', type='button', value='Click me!')
                li(down-at='16', chg-visib-at='16')
                  | Any HTML5 possibility:
                  div(style='text-align: center')
                    iframe(width='336', height='189', src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/qk00gbDwGqM', frameborder='0', allowfullscreen='')
                li(down-at='17', chg-visib-at='17')
                  | Any random CSS trick copy-pasted from the internet:
                  // Should certainly be in a separate file, but as it is random copy-pasted css, it is allowed here
                  style.
                    #container {
                    height: 200px;
                    width: 200px;
                    position:relative;
                    display:inline-block;
                    }
                    .square{
                    height: 94%;
                    width: 94%;
                    background: white;
                    position: absolute;
                    top: 50%;
                    left: 50%;
                    margin: -47% 0 0 -47%;
                    }
                    .black{
                    background: black;
                    animation: rotate 10s infinite linear;
                    }
                    @keyframes rotate{
                    0%{ transform: rotate(0deg); }
                    100%{ transform: rotate(360deg); }
                    }
                  div(style='margin-top:50px; text-align: center')
                    // Argh random copy-pasted html ...
                    #container
                      .square.black
                        .square
                          .square.black
                            .square
                              .square.black
                                .square
                                  .square.black
                                    .square
                                      .square.black
                                        .square
                                          .square.black
                                            .square
                                              .square.black
                                                .square
                                                  .square.black
                                                    .square
                                                      .square.black
                                                        .square
                                                          .square.black
                                                            .square
                                                              .square.black
                                                                .square
                                                                  .square.black
                                                                    .square
                                                                      .square.black
                                                                        .square
                                                                          .square.black
                                                                            .square
                                                                              .square.black
          // Still in the same slip, but somehow next part. Use of a usual html title (h1).
          h1(chg-visib-at='18', up-at='18') Slip.js advanced: fine control of events
          ul
            li(chg-visib-at='19')
              | It is easy to define custom functions to be called at precise time of the presentation:
              ul
                // highlight.js again messing with readability
                li At a given step of a slip,
                li(chg-visib-at='20') When refreshing the slip,
                li(chg-visib-at='21') When leaving or entering...
            li(chg-visib-at='22')
              | There are already some tools (such as a special querySelector which avoids querying inside subslips) and there will soon be many more!
            li(chg-visib-at='23')
              | The project is open-source and will (soon) be well-documented!
      .c1(chg-visib-at='4', style='font-size: 170px;position:absolute; top: 30%; left: 5%; right: 5%; background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9): border-radius: 5%;')
        div(style='margin: 100px')
          | Github: #[a(href='https://github.com/panglesd/slip-js') https://github.com/panglesd/slip-js].
        div(style='margin: 100px')
          | An example (old version of the engine): #[a(href='https://choum.net/panglesd/slides/slides-js/slides.html') Slips].
